node.text: Today, I spoke at the National Association for Drug Court Professionals, a charity that develops strategies within the judicial system that empower people to change their lives.  It wasn’t until I went to jail for some indiscretions that I knew I needed to change my life around.  I thank God every day for the professionals who disciplined me with compassion and fairness.  Thank you @nadcp for recognizing that we all make mistakes and could use a second chance in life.  Love. Light. Leslie.

node.text: I have so much to learn from my adored friend @brandicarlile, and I think that her struggle with a faith that once rejected her would provide comfort to many other souls as well. She learned to see past all the narrow peripherals of that faith to find and embrace its fundamental spirit.  She lives by that spirit today, and her music and her thrilling voice are an invitation to others to share her peace.  Please visit her page and grab your copy of Broken Horses which is out now.  You can also find our whole conversation where this video clip was taken.  Love. Light. Leslie. @thetanyatucker
